properties.documentation: Potential data consumers e.g. service providers can get all information from one point of access - NAP

element.name: Enhance road safety by providing higher quality traffic information to as many users as possible

properties.documentation:
• More public and private stakeholders involved in many EU MS with regular data exchange between them and used for creating high quality ITS services.
  • Easier and more regular data exchange (e.g. ID verification of content providers once)
  • Better quality of ITS services for end users
  • Optional: Introduce regular quality management of ITS services and data content feedback procedures

element.name: Exchange of road safety related data over the NAP

properties.documentation: All road safety related data shall be provided via the NAP for free at the point of use. Service provider may use them to increase road safety.
The improved quality of traffic organisation with many stakeholders leads overall to lower emissions and fuel comsumption.

element.name: The NAP is an easy to use central point of exchange for traffic related data between data provider and data consumers.

properties.documentation:
• NAP features shall be language independent (english + local language)
  • NAP supports the discovery of metadata and data samples without user registration
  • NAP supports data exchange based on standards
  • NAP fosters EU wide interoperable ITS services for travellers
  • NAP makes data available at standard interfaces and in machine readable formats
  • The NAP data content is extendable to all ITS-directive 2010/40 domains
  • The NAP does not infringe the rights of the data owner for the use of data, but can support the exchange (e.g. by a standardised licence, agreed terms and conditions, technical support with a machine-readable interface definition.)

element.name: Trans European high level Road transport network

properties.documentation: Transport Network Mainly trans European high level Road transport network and extensible to Public Transport and Interfaces ITS Service EU wide ITS services coverage with seamless handover between NAPs of the different member states for easier and consistent ITS service building at neighbouring regions, states and at EU level ITS Service Type RTTI services, static, dynamic data and information sets of public and private stakeholders Level of detail Organisational view of NAP stakeholders and their cooperation, including a functional definition of the ITS service at meta level and including their data content coverage/contribution in the defined ITS domain Perspective Policy perspective, with contribution from public and private stakeholders in the service development and delivery Focus Cooperations between roles and Information systems, interfaces and standards to foster regular data exchange
Traveller comfort and easier change of the transport mean.

properties.name: 02 NAP Functional View
properties.documentation:
All the functionality in this DFD exists at the same level. A detailed description is provided for each of the Low-Level Functions.
The Data Stores (D 3.15 and D3.16) are used to hold meta-data and pointers to static and dynamic road related data, details of which are included in their descriptions. This data is for use by the Low-Level Functions in this High-level Function.
